<span id="freeTextContainer16452342683089528039">Oh my, what a ridiculously entertaining, addictive read!<br/><br/>Erienne&apos;s sleazy father decides to sell her to the highest bidder in order to pay off his debt to the dashing Christopher Seton whom Erienne is determined to loathe. The person who buys the right to marry the gorgeous Erienne is the mysterious, scarred Lord Saxton, who marries her after paying 5,000 pounds. <br/><br/>A Beauty and the Beast set-up follows with Erienne growing to care for her husband who, despite refusing to remove his mask, treats her</span>
  <span id="freeText16452342683089528039" style="display:none">Oh my, what a ridiculously entertaining, addictive read!<br /><br />Erienne's sleazy father decides to sell her to the highest bidder in order to pay off his debt to the dashing Christopher Seton whom Erienne is determined to loathe. The person who buys the right to marry the gorgeous Erienne is the mysterious, scarred Lord Saxton, who marries her after paying 5,000 pounds. <br /><br />A Beauty and the Beast set-up follows with Erienne growing to care for her husband who, despite refusing to remove his mask, treats her with every consideration. Yet fate keeps throwing her together with the daring, charming Christopher and she finds herself irresistibly drawn to him, more and more attracted with every meeting. And Christopher keeps declaring his love. Soon, Erienne is imagining Christopher when she is sleeping with Lord Saxton!<br /><br />What's a gal to do when she seems to be in love with two men at once? Well, if she is Erienne, consider herself very very lucky. Because <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[of course, Christopher is Lord Saxton who has embarked on this masquerade in large part to win her heart. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />There are secret identities, birth secrets, masked highwaymen, evil parents, and delicious makeouts. In the middle of it all are a hero and heroine I have genuinely grown to love. Eirenne is pretty darn cool and Christopher is the only Woodiwiss hero I wouldn't mind taking home with me.<br /><br />So yeah - super super fun!</span>
