    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2554915547" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2554915547" />
    <a title="Irene" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/36459924-irene"><img alt="Irene" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627675581p2/36459924.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2554915547?book_show_action=true">Oct 09, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Irene" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Irene" href="/user/show/36459924-irene">Irene</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9780060728687" href="/book/show/7064372-a-rose-in-winter">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/36459924-irene?shelf=regency-romances-and-bodice-rippers">regency-romances-and-bodice-rippers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2554915547" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11302523992872129607">A Rose in Winter is a splendid Beauty and the Beast homage that is a classic in its own right. Fairy tale retellings can be hard to pull off, but well-played, Kathleen E. Woodiwiss! Woodiwiss transports the reader to an idyllic setting of medieval-ish England. Eirenne Fleming&apos;s loutish father has sold her in marriage to the highest bidder, and it is Lord Saxton, a man physically damaged after being caught in a horrific fire at his manor a few years ago, and now covers himself from head to toe. L</span>
  <span id="freeText11302523992872129607" style="display:none">A Rose in Winter is a splendid Beauty and the Beast homage that is a classic in its own right. Fairy tale retellings can be hard to pull off, but well-played, Kathleen E. Woodiwiss! Woodiwiss transports the reader to an idyllic setting of medieval-ish England. Eirenne Fleming's loutish father has sold her in marriage to the highest bidder, and it is Lord Saxton, a man physically damaged after being caught in a horrific fire at his manor a few years ago, and now covers himself from head to toe. Lord Saxton's troubles are far from over, however, as roaming bandits nip at his heels, and politicians continue to close in around him. There is a Night Rider stirring up trouble with his Robin Hood exploits, and Eirenne's rakish suitor, Christopher Seton, continues to pursue her, as he is Lord Saxton's cousin.<br /><br />I've never met a "hero has to pretend to be another person to the heroine" plot that I've liked, and A Rose In Winter proves to be no exception. What I can say, however, is that it didn't take away from the story because Christopher is a charmingly naughty suitor. For all the gothic atmosphere, A Rose In Winter has levity to it: Eirenne first meets Christopher, under the assumption that he is a suitor when in fact he is a sworn enemy of the family, and it is a hilarious meet-cute. <br /><br />I will definitely be picking up more of Woodweiss's stories in the future!</span>
  <a data-text-id="11302523992872129607" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


