<div id="review_89608014" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/89608014" />
    <a title="Maureen Feeney" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3191182-maureen-feeney"><img alt="Maureen Feeney" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1400769126p2/3191182.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/89608014?book_show_action=true">Feb 14, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maureen Feeney" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maureen Feeney" href="/user/show/3191182-maureen-feeney">Maureen Feeney</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3191182-maureen-feeney?shelf=own-it">own-it</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3191182-maureen-feeney?shelf=kathleen-e-woodiwiss">kathleen-e-woodiwiss</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer89608014" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer145940667382774891"> Predictable but still good. <br/><br/>QUICK SUMMARY<br/>This story reminded me of Beauty and the Beast a bit. Erienne Fleming&apos;s father is a drinker and a gambler and mayor of a small english town. Badly needing money to pay his gambling debts and tired of trying to get Erienne to marry money he sells her by public auction. Christopher Seton wants her but Erienne&apos;s father forbids him to bid because he is the one he owes the money to and Christopher accused him of cheating. Erienne flees before the auction and </span>
  <span id="freeText145940667382774891" style="display:none"> Predictable but still good. <br /><br />QUICK SUMMARY<br />This story reminded me of Beauty and the Beast a bit. Erienne Fleming's father is a drinker and a gambler and mayor of a small english town. Badly needing money to pay his gambling debts and tired of trying to get Erienne to marry money he sells her by public auction. Christopher Seton wants her but Erienne's father forbids him to bid because he is the one he owes the money to and Christopher accused him of cheating. Erienne flees before the auction and while in trouble she is rescued by Lord Saxon but he sends her home only to purchase her at the auction himself. Lord Saxon was badly burned in a fire but he is kind ,even though he disgusts Erienne she eventually starts getting feelings for him but Christopher wont leave her alone and she starts falling for him too.<br /><br />This is a great read and is well written. I only have a couple complaints, Erienne was too much of a victim, I never knew a Heroine to be rescued as much as she, and she was a bit shallow in that she judged all her suiters and Lord Saxon by their looks. I could also see the ending coming at me like a train, big and obvious. This is typical KEW but worth a nice rainy evening curled up on a chair.</span>
  <a data-text-id="145940667382774891" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


