<div id="review_218004738" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/218004738" />
    <a title="J.C. Cassels" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6523498-j-c-cassels"><img alt="J.C. Cassels" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1335470879p2/6523498.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/218004738?book_show_action=true">Oct 02, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="J.C. Cassels" class="user" itemprop="url" name="J.C. Cassels" href="/user/show/6523498-j-c-cassels">J.C. Cassels</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer218004738" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8049182724573045785">This book is one of my top five favorite Romances of all time, and brother, I&apos;ve read a LOT of them. <br/><br/>Beautiful Erienne Fleming is sold on the block to cover her family&apos;s debts. The stipulation is that she will be wedded to the man wealthy enough to satisfy the notes being held by charming gambler, Christopher Seton, who wants her for himself.<br/><br/>When Erienne is bought by the masked, crippled Lord Saxton, and properly wedded, she finds herself torn between two men: The vexing Seton, who happens to be</span>
  <span id="freeText8049182724573045785" style="display:none">This book is one of my top five favorite Romances of all time, and brother, I've read a LOT of them. <br /><br />Beautiful Erienne Fleming is sold on the block to cover her family's debts. The stipulation is that she will be wedded to the man wealthy enough to satisfy the notes being held by charming gambler, Christopher Seton, who wants her for himself.<br /><br />When Erienne is bought by the masked, crippled Lord Saxton, and properly wedded, she finds herself torn between two men: The vexing Seton, who happens to be somehow related to the Saxtons despite his Yankee upbringing, and the tender lover her badly scarred humpback of a husband turns out to be.<br /><br />That, in itself, would be a compelling enough story for me, but in typical Woodiwiss fashion, there is swashbuckling adventure and enough mystery to move this book from a simple Historical Romance to a Romance Classic and a must-read for any fan or would-be fan of the genre.<br /><br />Woodiwiss redefined the Historical Romance Genre. The formula followed by today's stars of the genre are only following the pattern set by Woodiwiss.<br /><br />Do I recommend this book? Absolutely. This one earned a place on my bookshelf nearly thirty years ago and it has become an old friend I turn to again and again.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8049182724573045785" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


