        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer416250224" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4963309155192760003">Classic-oh-so-very-classic historical romance with a non boring heroine and a quite mysterious plot!<br/><br/><b><u>UPDATE</u>: 09/17/2012</b><br/><br/>A Rose in Winter is a story full of intrigue, mystery, suspense and romance. <br/><br/><a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[<b>Erienne was...</b><br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380391503i/753944.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><b>But then she met yankee Christopher Seton.</b><br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380391503i/753945.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><b>...and he set her lust &amp; ire off!</b><br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753946.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><b>Then she met Lord Saxton...</b><br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753947.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><b>And married him!</b><br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753948.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><b>...and he set her <s>lust &amp; ire</s> off!</b><br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753949.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><b>But beside him there were things she had for granted.</b><br/><br/><span>[image error]</span><br/><br/><b>However he told her...</b> <br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380391503i/753951.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><b>...and she...</b><br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753952.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><b>Until Christopher Seton</b></span></span>
  <span id="freeText4963309155192760003" style="display:none">Classic-oh-so-very-classic historical romance with a non boring heroine and a quite mysterious plot!<br><br><b><u>UPDATE</u>: 09/17/2012</b><br><br>A Rose in Winter is a story full of intrigue, mystery, suspense and romance. <br><br><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[<b>Erienne was...</b><br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380391503i/753944.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>But then she met yankee Christopher Seton.</b><br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380391503i/753945.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>...and he set her lust &amp; ire off!</b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753946.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>Then she met Lord Saxton...</b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753947.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>And married him!</b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753948.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>...and he set her <s>lust &amp; ire</s> off!</b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753949.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>But beside him there were things she had for granted.</b><br><br><span>[image error]</span><br><br><b>However he told her...</b> <br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380391503i/753951.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>...and she...</b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753952.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>Until Christopher Seton's presence became too much and she...</b><br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380391503i/753953.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>Then Lord Saxton revealed to be Christoph-...</b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753954.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>...and Erienne's father said...</b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753955.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>But Lord Cristopher... Saxton sliced all enemies.</b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753956.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>And finally, <i>FINALLY</i>, they managed to...<b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753957.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>And...</b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380391503ra/753958.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>And...</b><br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380391503i/753959.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>And...</b><br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380391503i/753960.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>And...</b><br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380391503i/753961.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>- <i>THE END</i> -</b><br></b></b> <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br><br>Once upon a time it was the Flemings. After the mother's death, dad Avery started gambling away all their fortune, until they were forced to move to another city due to debts and his dismissal from his previous post. He continued his cheating in gambling and when a yankee called him upon it, dad Avery let son Farrell to duel with said yankee for the family's honor despite him being in the wrong. Losing the duel, most of his right arm's usage and his self-respect, son Farrell began gambling and drinking as well. That left the family with a single option: get daughter and sister Erienne married to a wealthy - preferrably old too - man, who will pay their debts to the yankee, Christopher Seton, off. After holding them back as much as possible, Erienne is being sold in an auction of sorts and the highest bidder, Lord Saxton, via his vessel <i>purchases</i> her hand in marriage.<br><br>Life as Lady Saxton is full of money, beautiful gowns and jewelry, outings and a husband with a most off-putting, horrifying presence. Masked, crippled and scarred, Lord Saxton terrifies Erienne. However, he never asks for anything, giving her time and space at her request. Erienne comes to love the yankee, Christopher Seton, who still tries to conquer her, and her awe-inspiring, mysterious hunsband, Lord Saxton, who woos her with his caring and kind demeanor.<br><br>In the meanwhile, several murders take place in town due to raidings, and a 'night rider' appears, who seems to be the cause of it all. The leads show a connection for all the events that take place: the Saxton family.<br><br>In this tale I admit I admired Erienne, because she carries herself with dignity, spite and spunk no matter the circumstances. Christopher Seton, gentleman, yankee and scoundrel extraordinaire, is a most charming man, winning the reader - and poor Erienne - over from the moment he shows up. It's impossible not to come to like though Lord Saxton as well. His mysterious, quiet yet thundering presence, holds an irresistible and undeniable allure. The respect and blatant love and admiration he shows towards Erienne add to his good points.<br><br>The story starts off simply. The daughter of a soon-to-be-poor family is being sold off to a wealthy man so that their debts will be paid. Slowly though it becomes much more intriguing and dangerous as more people show up with their own motives, ambitions and purposes. Through a series of events, others of higher and others of less importance, the momentum is conserved, simply switching from one focal point to the next. And it all explodes eventually giving a most satisfying conclusion to the story and its' participants. Needless to say that it's not only the plot that develops, but also the characters. From the first to the very last chapter, the reader realizes they've come a long way and are being judged by their own choices and actions.<br><br>If you're acquainted with Kathleen E. Woodiwiss' novels, you'll know that they're historical, old-fashioned romances, full of long, detailed descriptions and old english. The men are possessive brutes, knaves and/or lords. The women are dumb or witty depending on the role each character serves and the chronological boundaries the book is referring to. So, if by any chance you happen to like good, old, classic romance, here's the author and the book for you!</["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></span>
  <a data-text-id="4963309155192760003" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

