<div id="review_1068495338" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1068495338" />
    <a title="Dendera" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/33373863-dendera"><img alt="Dendera" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1408250314p2/33373863.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1068495338?book_show_action=true">May 18, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dendera" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dendera" href="/user/show/33373863-dendera">Dendera</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33373863-dendera?shelf=18th-century">18th-century</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33373863-dendera?shelf=5-stars">5-stars</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33373863-dendera?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33373863-dendera?shelf=action">action</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33373863-dendera?shelf=regency-romance">regency-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33373863-dendera?shelf=adult">adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33373863-dendera?shelf=gothic-romance">gothic-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33373863-dendera?shelf=adventure">adventure</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33373863-dendera?shelf=arranged-marriages">arranged-marriages</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33373863-dendera?shelf=fast-paced">fast-paced</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1068495338" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12695100445551914304">*** 10 stars read ***<br/><br/>If I could give this book 10 stars I definitely would! It was enthralling in every way possible, the storyline, characters, the love, the emotions,the humour, the prose... I simply could not put this novel down and it kept me reading very late into the night. For me, this is a sign of a 5 ++ star read right away! I loved how Kathleen Woodiwiss was able to give us a very unique love story and at the same time weave into it mystery, action, suspense, and humour. All the elemen</span>
  <span id="freeText12695100445551914304" style="display:none">*** 10 stars read ***<br /><br />If I could give this book 10 stars I definitely would! It was enthralling in every way possible, the storyline, characters, the love, the emotions,the humour, the prose... I simply could not put this novel down and it kept me reading very late into the night. For me, this is a sign of a 5 ++ star read right away! I loved how Kathleen Woodiwiss was able to give us a very unique love story and at the same time weave into it mystery, action, suspense, and humour. All the elements that comprise some of the greatest romance novels. The best element about 'A Rose in Winter' is its uniqueness in how the hero assumed two identities to win the heroine's love. It's a very special type of storyline for the courting of the hero and heroine and of how their love flourished. When you come across a storyline that you've never encountered before, it's a sign of a masterpiece!<br /><br />Did anyone else who read this story find Erienne's cheapskate father hilarious?<br /><br />The only other book I'd read by Kathleen Woodiwiss was 'Shanna'. And that was many years ago, but I remember giving it only 3 stars back then. After being captivated by 'A Rose in Winter', I know I'll give 'Shanna' a second chance and Kathleen Woodiwiss's novels won't stay on my to-read shelves for long!</span>
  <a data-text-id="12695100445551914304" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


