        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer57481776" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13222007546666193522">This was Kathleen Woodwiss&apos;s Beauty and the Beast book. Erienne&apos;s father gave her hand in marriage to the richest lord in the land, Lord Saxon. Rumors abound about him being half beast and half man. As Erienne finds the courage to go fourth with the marriage in order to save her family, she has to let go the secret in her heart where Christopher Seaton, sassy Yankee that he is, had started to make a place for himself. On the other, Erienne finds herself finding herself having feeling for her rav</span>
  <span id="freeText13222007546666193522" style="display:none">This was Kathleen Woodwiss's Beauty and the Beast book. Erienne's father gave her hand in marriage to the richest lord in the land, Lord Saxon. Rumors abound about him being half beast and half man. As Erienne finds the courage to go fourth with the marriage in order to save her family, she has to let go the secret in her heart where Christopher Seaton, sassy Yankee that he is, had started to make a place for himself. On the other, Erienne finds herself finding herself having feeling for her ravaged and deformed husband as well. Is it possible for a woman to love two men so completely? Timeless fairy tale and one of my absolute favs. My 28 year old copy still looks good for a oversize trade paperback. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13222007546666193522" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

